    1,
    'Bipolar I disorder (manic episode >7 days with functional impairment): manic symptoms without antidepressant for this episode. NICE NG185: acute mania — first-line: atypical antipsychotic (olanzapine, quetiapine, risperidone). Haloperidol is an alternative. Stop antidepressants (can precipitate cycling). Lithium or valproate can be started for long-term mood stabilisation. Assess for substance use, thyroid function, and family history. Admit if risk to self or others.',
