    'GAD: excessive, uncontrollable worry across multiple domains for >6 months + 3/6 physical symptoms (restlessness, fatigue, difficulty concentrating, irritability, muscle tension, sleep disturbance). NICE NG197: step 1 — psychoeducation and self-help. Step 2 — high-intensity CBT (worry postponement, relaxation, cognitive restructuring) or SSRI/SNRI (sertraline, escitalopram, venlafaxine). Both equally effective. Step 3 — combination or add pregabalin. Benzodiazepines are NOT recommended long-term.',
